This paper is about the optimization of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning subfield of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the landscape of multilayer neural networks and how stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and over-parameterization affect the optimization process. Based on this information, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
